Events.Text: Say hallo to the AI Assistant. [instruction 1 of 6]
Hello, I'm Alexis.
How can I help you Alexis?
How can I help you Alexis?
I am interested in viewing an apartment. Specifically, One on Center Apartments.
You suddenly remember that you have a friend's wedding on Friday at 9 pm. [instruction 2 of 6]
What day and time are you interested in viewing?
What day and time are you interested in viewing?
I wanted to come on Friday at 9 pm. Oh no, wait! I can't do it that day because my friend is getting married then.
Ask something about the apartment, or engage in smalltalk, or make a joke. [instruction 3 of 6]
Do you have another day and time in mind?
Do you have another day and time in mind?
Wanna hear a joke? Why do we tell actors to "break a leg"?  Because every play has a cast. Hahaha

You cannot remember if you had payed the application fee. Find a way to make an appointment anyway. If no date is available, change date and/or time until something works. If you already got the appointment, engage in smalltalk. [instruction 4 of 6]
That's great. Do you still want to schedule a viewing?
That's great. Do you still want to schedule a viewing?
Yes. How about Thursday at 9 pm?
Once you've scheduled the viewing, say something about your friend's wedding. [instruction 5 of 6]
fee
Have you already paid the application fee for the apartment?
I don't remember if I payed the application fee. Can I still make an appointment?
When you are done with all the instructions, bring the conversation to a natural close.  [instruction 6 of 6]
available
Great, there is still a viewing available at that time. Would you like me to book it for you?
Yes, please.
